  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nUsing azureFile volume after 1.8.x mount the share onto host with both dir_mode and file_mode options set to 0700, which was changed in this commit.\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/commit/4378c7ae8eb94b47db31b9846bf72a0e2e020270#diff-b99f7ac20a1bc605e253dfde484cee68\r\n\r\nThis disallow any container run with non root user (which is the suggested way to run app) to access the contents.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nThe mode should at least set to 755 or even 777, which seem to be fine since we can still configure `accessMode` of volume or `readOnly` of volumeMount.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nUse azureFile at 1.8.x up versions.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/45337 might solve this too, but closed :(\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"8\", GitVersion:\"v1.8.2\", GitCommit:\"bdaeafa71f6c7c04636251031f93464384d54963\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2017-10-24T21:07:53Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.9.1\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"darwin/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"8\", GitVersion:\"v1.8.2\", GitCommit:\"bdaeafa71f6c7c04636251031f93464384d54963\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2017-10-24T19:38:10Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.8.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: Bare metal on Azure VM\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Ubuntu 16.04.2\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): Linux  #114-Ubuntu SMP Tue Aug 8 11:56:56 UTC 2017 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n- Install tools: kubeadm\r\n- Others:\r\n",
